OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1775747465
OL,3,CVictims and bereaved families given
OL,4,Cmore time to challenge sentences
OL,6,FVictims and bereaved families will be
OL,7,Fgiven more time to challenge sentences
OL,8,Fthey think are too lenient, the
OL,9,Fgovernment has announced.
OL,11,FUnder new plans, they will have six
OL,12,Fmonths to ask for a sentence to be
OL,13,Freconsidered ` a significant increase
OL,14,Fon the current 28-day limit, the
OL,15,FMinistry of Justice (MOJ) said.
OL,17,FFamilies and victims cannot be
OL,18,Fexpected to engage with the justice
OL,19,Fsystem in such a short period of time,
OL,20,Fministers believe.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/6
