OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1775747465
OL,3,CVictims and bereaved families given
OL,4,Cmore time to challenge sentences
OL,6,FReforms to the Unduly Lenient Sentence
OL,7,FScheme will give them more time to ask
OL,8,Fthe attorney general and solicitor
OL,9,Fgeneral to refer a sentence in the
OL,10,Fpublic interest to the Court of Appeal.
OL,12,FOther members of the public will still
OL,13,Fonly have 28 days to refer a case.
OL,15,FWelcoming the move, Victims'
OL,16,FCommissioner Claire Waxman said the
OL,17,Fchange is long overdue.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
